<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/2585</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-30">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1342. Your 1789, 15th.<note n="2" xml:id="d507fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>. <ref target="#pg_344">p.
                                    344</ref>.</note> Have consignments actually been placed in
                                prize court? If so, report date and reasons assigned. If not, Inform
                                Foreign Office owners protest and request release on ground goods
                                were shipped in neutral trade between neutral countries and were not
                                contraband.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>